Class RDKitDiversityPickerNodeModel

  • java.lang.Object

    public class RDKitDiversityPickerNodeModel
extends AbstractRDKitSplitterNodeModel
    This class implements the node model of the RDKitDiversityPicker node providing filtering based on the open source RDKit library.
    Author:
    Greg Landrum, Manuel Schwarze

      • createInputDataInfos

        protected InputDataInfo[] createInputDataInfos(int inPort,
                                               DataTableSpec inSpec)
                                        throws InvalidSettingsException
        This method needs to be implemented by a concrete node to generate InputDataInfo objects for each input column for all input tables. To find the proper column, the concrete node implementation must pass in the appropriate setting model of the column name into the constructor of the InputDataInfo class. This implementation generates input data info object for the input column and connects it with the information coming from the appropriate setting model.
        Specified by:
        createInputDataInfos in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inPort - The port number of the input table to create input data objects for.
        inSpec - The table specification of the input table. Can be null.
        Returns:
        An array of info objects for all columns used as input for the passed table. Should not return null. If no input columns are used from the passed table, it should return an empty array.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if the current settings or the spec of the input table will make it impossible to process the data.

      • preProcessing

        protected void preProcessing(BufferedDataTable[] inData,
                             InputDataInfo[][] arrInputDataInfo,
                             ExecutionContext exec)
                      throws java.lang.Exception
        This method gets called from the method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.execute(BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext), before the row-by-row processing starts. All necessary pre-calculations can be done here. Results of the method should be made available through member variables, which get picked up by the other methods like process(InputDataInfo[], DataRow) in the factory or AbstractRDKitNodeModel.postProcessing(BufferedDataTable[], InputDataInfo[][], BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext) in the model. This implementation calculates what rows to keep.
        Overrides:
        preProcessing in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inData - The input tables of the node.
        arrInputDataInfo - Information about all columns of the input tables.
        exec - The execution context, which was derived as sub-execution context based on the percentage setting of #getPreProcessingPercentage(). Track the progress from 0..1.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Thrown, if pre-processing fails.

      • cleanupIntermediateResults

        protected void cleanupIntermediateResults()
        This method gets called at the very end of the node execution. It is called also after the user canceled the execution. It can be overridden to cleanup all intermediate results, e.g. arrays, which have been created to pass over values from pre-processing to processing to post-processing steps. Always check for null before calling cleanup functionality on resources. They may have never instancianted, if the user canceled before the resource was created. By default, this method is not doing anything. Exceptions thrown from this method will be caught and logged as a warning, but will not have any effect on the process flow.
        Overrides:
        cleanupIntermediateResults in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel

      • createWarningContextOccurrencesMap

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Long> createWarningContextOccurrencesMap(BufferedDataTable[] inData,
                                                                                            InputDataInfo[][] arrInputDataInfo,
                                                                                            BufferedDataTable[] resultData)
        Description copied from class: AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Creates a map with information about occurrences of certain contexts, which are registered in the warning consolidator. Such a context could for instance be the "row context", if the warning consolidator was configured with it and consolidates warnings that happen based on certain malformed data in input rows. In this case we would list the row number of the input table (inData[0]) for this row context. The passed in parameters are for convenience only, as most of the time the numbers depend on them to some degree. The default implementation delivers a map, which contains only one context - the ROW_CONTEXT of the consolidator - and as total number of occurrences the number of input rows in table 0. Override this method for differing behavior.
        Overrides:
        createWarningContextOccurrencesMap in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inData - All input tables of the node with their data.
        arrInputDataInfo - Information about all columns in the input tables.
        resultData - All result tables of the node that will be returned by the execute() method.
        Returns:
        Map with number of occurrences of different contexts, e.g. encountered rows during processing.
        See Also:
        AbstractRDKitNodeModel.getWarningConsolidator()

      • determineTargetTable

        public int determineTargetTable(int iInPort,
                                long lRowIndex,
                                DataRow row,
                                InputDataInfo[] arrInputDataInfo,
                                long lUniqueWaveId)
        This method implements the condition on which data are split between multiple output tables or filtered out completely. This implementation filters out all rows, which are not contained in the rowsToKeep member variable, which was calculated during the pre-processing phase.
        Specified by:
        determineTargetTable in interface SplitCondition
        Specified by:
        determineTargetTable in class AbstractRDKitSplitterNodeModel
        Parameters:
        arrInputDataInfo - Input data information about all columns of the table at the input port. Not used in this implementation.
        lUniqueWaveId - A unique id that should be used for marking RDKit objects for cleanup. Marked objects will be cleaned up automatically at the end of this call. If this is not wanted, the objects should either not be marked for cleanup or they should be marked without an id, which would lead to a cleanup at the end of the entire execution process. Not used in this implementation.
        iInPort - The input port of the data in focus. Rather an informal value.
        lRowIndex - The row index of the row being processed.
        row - The complete data row in focus. Normally a decision is made based on information in this row.
        Returns:
        0 to keep the row, or -1 if row shall be filtered out completely.
